Section 1:
1 L.D. 1187
2 Date: (Filing No. H- )
3 CRIMINAL JUSTICE AND PUBLIC SAFETY
5 STATE OF MAINE
6 HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES
7 132ND LEGISLATURE
8 FIRST SPECIAL SESSION
9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 792, L.D. 1187, “An Act to Require
10 Certain Mental Health Data to Be Included in Uniform Crime Reports”
11 Amend the bill by striking out the title and substituting the following:
12 'An Act to Include Certain Mental Health Data in Firearm Fatalities and
13 Hospitalizations Reports'
14 Amend the bill by striking out everything after the enacting clause and inserting the
15 following:
16 'Sec. 1. 22 MRSA c. 256-A, headnote is amended to read:
17 CHAPTER 256-A
18 REPORTING OF FIREARM FATALITIES AND, HOSPITALIZATIONS AND
19 MENTAL HEALTH REFERRALS
20 Sec. 2. 22 MRSA §1425, as amended by PL 2021, c. 676, Pt. A, §32, is further
21 amended by amending the section headnote to read:
22 §1425. Annual report on firearm fatalities and, hospitalizations and mental health
23 referrals
24 Sec. 3. 22 MRSA §1425, sub-§1, ¶C, as enacted by PL 2021, c. 369, §1, is
25 amended to read:
26 C. Unintentional discharges, further separated by the ages of the victims; and
27 Sec. 4. 22 MRSA §1425, sub-§2, as amended by PL 2021, c. 676, Pt. A, §32, is
28 further amended to read:
29 2. Hospitalizations. Hospitalizations that occurred as a result of a firearm but did not
30 result in death.; and
Page 1 - 132LR1802(02)
COMMITTEE AMENDMENT
COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 792, L.D. 1187
1 Sec. 5. 22 MRSA §1425, sub-§3 is enacted to read:
2 3. Mental health referrals. The number of mental health referrals made for
3 individuals assessed as presenting a likelihood of foreseeable harm pursuant to Title 34-B,
4 section 3862-A, including the number of individuals receiving treatment or services
5 pursuant to those referrals.
6 Sec. 6. Appropriations and allocations. The following appropriations and
7 allocations are made.
8 HEALTH AND HUMAN SERVICES, DEPARTMENT OF
9 Mental Health Services - Community Z198
10 Initiative: Provides one-time funding for technology costs to develop systems for data
11 collection and reporting of referrals to mental health treatment or services made by medical
12 practitioners for individuals in protective custody found to present a likelihood of
13 foreseeable harm to self or others.
14 GENERAL FUND 2025-26 2026-27
15 All Other $1,875,219 $0
16 __________ __________
17 GENERAL FUND TOTAL $1,875,219 $0
1184 '
19 Amend the bill by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or section
20 number to read consecutively.
21 SUMMARY
2222 This amendment, which is the majority report of the committee, replaces the bill and
2233 changes the title. The amendment requires that the annual report on firearm fatalities and
2244 hospitalizations, provided by the Director of the Maine Center for Disease Control and
2255 Prevention within the Department of Health and Human Services, include the number of
2266 mental health referrals made for individuals assessed as presenting a likelihood of
2277 foreseeable harm and the number of individuals receiving treatment or services pursuant to
2288 those referrals. The amendment also adds an appropriations and allocations section.
2299 FISCAL NOTE REQUIRED
3300 (See attached)
