21 SUMMARY
2222 This amendment, which is the majority report of the committee, replaces the bill and
2233 changes the title. The amendment requires that the annual report on firearm fatalities and
2244 hospitalizations, provided by the Director of the Maine Center for Disease Control and
2255 Prevention within the Department of Health and Human Services, include the number of
2266 mental health referrals made for individuals assessed as presenting a likelihood of
2277 foreseeable harm and the number of individuals receiving treatment or services pursuant to
2288 those referrals. The amendment also adds an appropriations and allocations section.
